commentTextItems.html: driven to long on, that's it, Zimbabwe win it

commentPostTextItems.html: Valiant run-chase from the Holland batsmen, but 301 was always going to be imposing.
Zimbabwe win by 99 runs here at Queens, an all-round polished performance from the victors
The Netherlands gave their most, great effort both in the field and with the bat
Please stay with us for the presentation.
Both teams on a lap of honour
Heath Streak takes home the Man of the Match award for that quick- fire knock of 44 (22), and his efforts both in the field and with the ball (10-1-36-1)
Thank you for joining us here at Queens Sports Club, be sure to join us for our next Bulawayo fixture: Pakistan v Zimbabwe, 4 March 2003 at 0730 GMT
From Cricinfo in Bulawayo, thank you and good day

milestones.description: Lefebvre and Henk-Jan Mol's 42-run partnership is NED's highest for the 8th wicket in ODIs, breaking the record of 28 between Lefebvre and Scholte
Tim de Leede has conceded the most runs in an innings (69) in ODIs for NED, going past Bakker's record of 64
Jeroen Smits has broken the record for most dismissals (4) in ODIs for NED, going past Marcel Schewe's 3
Tim de Leede has broken the record for playing the most ODIs (12) for NED, going past Bas Zuiderent
